ontea” 31.11\">Refs</a>]: <i>perfect</i> πεφόβημαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.510, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>pluperfect</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>plural</i> ἐπεφόβηντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 7.4.32, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.50 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Epic dialect</i> πεφοβήατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.206. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1> <i>active</i>, in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus (never in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] always in the sense <b>put to flight,</b> [ἴρηξ] ἐφόβησε κολοιούς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.583 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; [Ζεὺς] καὶ ἄλκιμον ἄνδρα φοβεῖ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 689; Τρώων οὓς ἐφόβησας 22.11; φοβῆσαίτε στίχας ἀνδρῶν 17.505; σὸς δόλος.. ἐφόβησε δὲ λαούς 15.15; σέ γέ φημι.. δουρὶ φοβῆσαι 20.187; once in 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus, φοβέεσκον ἐπὶ χθονὶ φῦλ᾽ ἀνθρώπων [prev. cited] \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>terrify, alarm,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.235, etc.; μὴ φίλους φόβει 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 262; ᾧ μή 'στι δρῶντι τάρβος οὐδ᾽ ἔπος φοβεῖ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 296, compare 1013, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 572 (Lyric poetry); ἡ δύναμις τῶν νέων φοβοῦσά τινας 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 4.3.2; αἱ κάμηλοι ἐφόβουν τους ἵππους 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.1.48; ρὸν Ἀλκιβιάδην ἐφόβουν, μὴ.. ἐπαγάγωνται 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.45; with _dative_ modi, λόγοις 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 215 (troch.); μεγαληγορίαισι φρένας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 357 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τῷ μὲν Τισσαφέρνει τοὺς Ἀθηναίους φ., ἐκείνοις δὲ τὸν Τισσαφέρνην <b>to frighten</b> the Athenians with T., and T. with the Athenians, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.82 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; with <i>participle</i>, λέγοντες φ. τινάς <b>by</b> saying, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitum magistro” 1.8; λέγοντες ὡς ἥξει βασιλεύς D 14.25: _absolutely_, πόνος ὁ μὴ φοβῶν κράτιστος 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 864 (Lyric poetry), φοβήσαντες κατεστήσαντο τὴν πολιτείαν \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>by terror,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 551b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> c.<i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>threaten with,</b> φ. λιμόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 6.51. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1> <i>passive</i> and <i>middle</i>, in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] always in the sense <b>to be put to flight</b> (compare [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Scholia A 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.223, +others), once in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”, κύνες.. διὰ σταθμοῖο φόβηθεν 16.163; frequently in 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad”, ὑπέμειναν ἀολλέες οὐδὲ φόβηθεν 5.498; τοὶ δ᾽ ἐφόβηθεν.. θεσπεσίῳ ὁμάδῳ 16.294; κὰμ μέσσον πεδίον φοβέοντο βόες ὣς ἅς τε λέων ἐφόβησε 11.172 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also <i>participle</i>, μὴ καὶ πεφοβημένος ἔλθης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 10.510, compare 15.4, 21.606; φοβηθεὶς δύσεθ᾽ ἁλὸς κατὰ κῦμα \">Refs</a>]<b>in flight,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6.135; βῆ δὲ φοβηθείς 22.137: ὑπό τινος φοβέεσθαι\">Refs</a>] <b>to flee</b> before him,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8.149; 